The oak treasure chest can be built in the treasure chest space of the costume room in a player-owned house. It requires 48 Construction to build and when built, it gives 120 experience. The player must have a hammer and a saw in their inventory to build it.

The oak treasure chest can hold storable rewards from Treasure Trails up to easy difficulty (level 1).

Storable rewards[edit | edit source]

Item sets from the Grand Exchange cannot be stored in a treasure chest, even if all of the components can be stored within the Treasure chest.

This list contains all items that can be stored in treasure chests of any tier.

Not storeable[edit | edit source]

  • Gnomish firelighters (including the Gnomish firelighter)
  • God pages
  • Purple sweets
  • Master scroll book
  • Ornament kits
  • Items that can be found elsewhere, such as food or runes
